//Call out Optional Actions with btn-info
//Bootstrap comes with several pre-defined colors for buttons. 
//The 'btn-info' class is used to call attention to optional actions that the user can take.

//Create a new block-level Bootstrap button below your 'Like' button with the text 'Info', and add Bootstrap's 'btn-info' class to it.

//Note that these buttons still need the 'btn' and 'btn-block' classes.

//BOOTSTRAP CODE:
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lobster" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: Lobster, Monospace;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: Monospace;
  }

  .thick-green-border {
    border-color: green;
    border-width: 10px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-radius: 50%;
